    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>March 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5613&#47;1853</date>.</p>
			<p>Dear sir and friend&#33;</p>
			<p>I transmit you herewith an advertisement which you<lb/> will please to insert in your Occident for <date><hi rend="underline">April</hi></date> if it<lb/> arrives in time. I will <add>Hebrew</add> come myself to <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> and would be very glad to find you there. My Dear father who<lb/> will arrive there&#8212;I hope&#8212;about the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of April</date> would also<lb/> be very happy to make your acquaintance and if you agree<lb/> to take part of his stock of hebrew books in commisison<lb/> he would probably give you all inducement&#38; facilities possible.<lb/> A notice&#44; about as follows would perhaps be proper in your Occident<lb/> &#8220;Large arrived of hebrew Books.</p>
			<p><persName>Mr. I. I. Bush</persName> the father of <persName role="author">Mr Isidor Bush</persName> now in <placeName>St Louis</placeName><lb/> who has been for many years the proprietor of the largest Hebrew<lb/> Printing Establishment &#40;v. Schmidt in <placeName>Vienna</placeName>&#41; and has edited a great<lb/> number of valuable hebrew works is expected to arrive this month from <placeName>Vienna</placeName>.<lb/> The old gentleman wishes to pass the evening of his life with<lb/> his only son in this home of the free&#59; and we bid him welcome.<lb/> He brings with him a large assortment of hebrew Books&#44;<lb/> mostly Bibles and Prayerbooks for the german and polish minhag<lb/> <sic>ellegantly</sic> bound. As <persName>Mr Bush</persName> intends to go west and to<lb/> stay a few days only at <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; we call the attention of<lb/> those who deal in Sphorim&#44; and others who want to purchase<lb/> to his advertisement.</p>
			<p>In regard to congregational affairs I request you to insert<lb/> the following communications filling the blank according<lb/> to your <sic>judgement</sic>&#44; as you have certainly received the printed<lb/> copy of the constitution&#44; which I have sent you.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>A good Translation of the Introduction or Preamble on Ist Article<lb/> would perhaps be of some interest to the public at large<lb/> and your readers in particular and would at the same time be<lb/> very <sic>wellcome</sic> to us here&#44; as we intend to print our constitution<lb/> in English also and a correct translation&#8212;in spirit more than word&#8212;<lb/> would be a task which I could not undertake to solve.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>&#8212;The Bnai&#45;El congregation&#44; lately formed by a union<lb/> of two former congregations here&#44; have adopted a constitution...<lb/>............<lb/>..........<lb/> and duly elected there after the following gentlemen as Trustees<lb/> <persName role="author">Mr. I. Bush</persName>&#44; <persName>D Block</persName>&#44; <persName>Is. Lowman</persName>&#44; <persName>A Suss</persName>&#44; <persName>L Schwarzkopf</persName>&#44; <persName>B Singer</persName><lb/> and <persName>W Walter</persName>&#44; from whom <persName>Mr Walter</persName> has been appointed President<lb/> <persName>Mr Suss</persName> Secretary <persName>Mr Lowman</persName> Treasurer. There have been also<lb/> elected different committees&#58; one for the erecting of a Syna<lb/>gogue and getting up a subscription to that effect&#44; one for a better<lb/> organization of the Ritual&#44; one committee for the burial of<lb/> the dead&#44; and so on. It is to be hoped that the com<lb/>mittees and officers will perform their respective duties with<lb/> pious zeal and promote thereby the objects expressed by<lb/> their constitution. <persName>Mr L Schwarzkopf</persName> has been elected<lb/> Chasan of the congregation and the service is well attended<lb/> on every <date>sabbath</date> since.</p>
			<p>Dear Sir&#8212;full liberty is given to you to speak more on these<lb/> subjects or to change the wording&#8212;according to your best<lb/> belief. For the &#44;&#44;advertisements&#8221; I will pay you&#44; of course</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">very respectfully your friend &#38; servant</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Isidore Bush</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><hi rend="underline">Advertisement&#58;</hi></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">The largest stock of</p>
			<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">Hebrew Books</hi></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">that was probably ever brought to this country</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">is to arrive during these days &#40;about <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of April</date>&#41;</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">and will be sold&#44; wholesale&#44; <hi rend="underline">at very low prices</hi></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">It contains chumashin&#44; Tenachs&#44; Machsorin</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">Tefillas &#38;c&#44; &#38;c. of the celebrated <placeName>Vienna</placeName> Editor&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">all bound in very elegant <sic>stile</sic></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">Dealers in <add>&#63;</add> will never find again such a favorable opor</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">tunity and will do well therefore to call personally or give</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">orders to their <placeName>New York</placeName> friends&#44; to purchase for them&#59;</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">it being the intention of the Importer <persName><hi rend="underline">Mr I. I. Bush</hi></persName></p>
			<p rend="align(center)">from <placeName>Vienna</placeName>&#44; to dispose of them during <hi rend="underline">a few days</hi> for cash</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">on good&#44; approved paper. The place of sale will</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">probably be at <persName>Mr Petshaw&#39;s</persName> Bookstore&#44; or if elsewhere</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">will be advertised in the daily Papers.</p>
          
        </body>
